    %% ============================================================================
    %% NOTES
    %% ============================================================================
    %%
    %% KEY CONCEPTS:
    %%
    %% 1. Streams are NOT triggers:
    %%    - Streams are a table-like object that RECORDS changes
    %%    - Reading from a stream advances the offset (consumes changes)
    %%    - Multiple tasks can read same stream (create separate streams)
    %%
    %% 2. Stream offset management:
    %%    - Offset advances ONLY when transaction commits successfully
    %%    - If task fails, offset unchanged, data reprocessed next run
    %%    - Ensures exactly-once processing (no data loss)
    %%
    %% 3. Task scheduling:
    %%    - SCHEDULE = 'USING CRON 0 * * * * UTC' (cron syntax)
    %%    - SCHEDULE = '5 MINUTE' (simple interval)
    %%    - AFTER task_name (DAG dependency)
    %%    - WHEN condition (e.g., SYSTEM$STREAM_HAS_DATA)
    %%
    %% 4. Serverless vs. Warehouse tasks:
    %%    - Serverless: Snowflake manages compute, pay per second
    %%    - Warehouse: You manage warehouse, more control
    %%    - Serverless is simpler for most use cases
    %%
    %% 5. Cost optimization:
    %%    - Use WHEN SYSTEM$STREAM_HAS_DATA to skip empty runs
    %%    - Set auto-suspend to 60 seconds on ETL warehouses
    %%    - Use Small/Medium warehouses (tasks are usually lightweight)
    %%    - Monitor with TASK_HISTORY to identify expensive tasks
    %%
    %% PERFORMANCE TIPS:
